title_x: Quality Item, but may not protect sides of the glass as well as other cases
text: This is the first OtterBox case I have tried.  The quality seems quite good and case fits good around the Samsung Note 8 phone.  A couple of cases I tried before seemed to come up around the edges too much, so that you couldn't use a glass protector, as the case would interfere with the protector and it would not sit tight to the glass.  This case seems to be designed in such a way that you could use a glass protector.  The problem is that because the case doesn't really cover the edges that well, if you were to drop the phone on the edge, it might break the glass. (Glass replacement for this phone is about $400 I have been told.)  I prefer a case that has a cover too, rather than a one sided case like this.  The problem with cases with a cover is that you always have to deal with the cover.  It can be a separate piece that you have to set aside when using the phone or a billfold type that you open up and then the cover is in your way when taking pictures.  If you like single sided cases so that your phone is always open for use, this is probably one of the best you can get.

Only one negative—it’s hard to take screenshots as there is too much of the wallet close to the upper right iPhone power button, which is needed to take screenshots. Maybe they can fix it. Still a great product and a great buy. I’ve had phone wallets for many years. This is by far the best. Would by again. Highly recommend!

title_x: Clear Case Shows Fingerprints; Provides Drop Protection Without Adding Bulk
text:
This OTTERBOX SYMMETRY SERIES CASE (CLEAR) fits my Samsung Galaxy S9 phone snugly, but is still fairly easy to remove (if necessary). It provides decent protection from short drops, and doesn’t add a lot of bulk or weight to the phone. The case back is totally clear (displaying the phone’s metal back), and the case sides are cloudy white (like etched art glass).

The thing to remember about a clear case, is that it shows fingerprints! When you install this case, you should avoid touching the INSIDE of the case, or else your inside fingerprints will show up prominently after the case is installed. To remove fingerprints from the inside or the outside of this case, use a microfiber cloth.

This is one-piece case. It covers only the back and sides of the phone, and it doesn’t include a screen protector. The raised case rim provides minimal protection for the display when the phone is laid face down on a flat surface. The phone’s buttons are covered by the case sides, but the buttons still work fine.

title_x: Aesthetic’s meet protection all wrapped into one..!!
text:
This is a great way to mix protection necessity with a trendy aesthetic! Offered in fun bright colors… and done using a thin silicone layer that is reinforced and designed to withstand impact. Case has raised lip around the camera to protect camera lenses from direct impact- this also accommodates for a protective glass over the front screen.. all without creating unnecessary bulk or exposed edges.

Love the grab this has in the hand.. nothing slippery to easily drop! This like to cling and create a nice grip- huge when multitasking!! Easy to put into place… all buttons and commands respond as expected. For a price point under $20 definitely a solid go to for those who like to add a little personality while protecting their investment! Hoping info helps decision- stay safe everyone.

title_x: Perfect for those always needing a charge on the go!!
text:
Wow! This IS really perfectly small.. I am absolutely smitten!! Of course, its a fraction bigger all the way around than a credit card.. and a tad wider but, yes! To the naked eye it would call it “credit card” size! (For any trying to fit/measure..)

To point out the impressive:
•Fits into a pocket comfortably and wont weigh down your pants!

•Easy to travel with as it practically has zero footprint.

•Fully charged within hours… Plug in overnight and it’s ready the next day.

•Love built in cord options- careful not to bend or tweak.. and you’ll have a charge worthy cord as needed!

•Can boost/replenish phone 0% back to 100%.. dependent on type of cell phone- x1 full complete charge- with battery juice left over..!!

•Cords come attached- 2 diff user ends!
(X1 iPhone/x1 Android!)

•Can be used as battery boosting source to so many items besides phones: fan, speaker, pads, light source, etc.

•can charge 2 devices at one time.

•Perfect price point for gift giving option or a self spoiler at $26- 100% user-friendly convenience in its size and on the go needs.

A few quirks:

•Cord connection could fit smoother- it depends on the device but.. it can be sticky.

•Charge cord is short! limits position while charging-especially if charging and using at same time.

•Bc of size- it can hold charge for only x1+ items to refuel..it doesn’t have capacity to hold multiple charges w/out a refill itself.

As you can see- perks outweigh the quirks in such a big way.. and the improvements are all doable. Great option- ideal for those wanting ease and convenience on the go! Hoping this info can help make your decision.. stay safe everyone.

text:
Thank you ORIbox.. for providing a quality protective phone case to those who haven’t upgraded their cellphone with each new release-
Believe it or not, some of us still use an 8+ ...

Looking for a reliable/substantial protective layer that will help eliminate damage caused by the accidental drop- this case does just that.

Love the reinforced corners as, they usually take the brunt of most drops- these are done with quality and without adding extra bulk.

Love the raised edge around the screen as well as, the camera… Even using i’ll level 9 glass screen protector, this still has enough of a raised edge to keep glass safe.

The case is pliable to get on.. yet, rigid to keep the phone feeling secure- love that. Trust me, there is no wiggle room when putting on the case! As per the Apple store… This lends peace of mind to the security The case will provide. They gave me a stamp of approval on my protective purchase!!

When buying a sleek/sexy looking phone, It seems criminal to cover it up… This is why I love the clear see-through material of the case. It provides a protective layer while looking invisible- boom!! Well done..
Best of all, the $ is reasonable.. you can’t go wrong! This does what you want, without breaking the bank…all while looking good! Win. Win. Win.

text:
I selected this case for a new iPhone 13. I wanted a case that fit snugly and that provided decent protection for my phone. So far I'm pleased with it.

This is a very simple case, providing basic protection. It has softer bumpers on the sides to protect against corner drops and the back is more rigid. While the sides are clear, the back is frosted which softens the appearance of the phone though the Apple logo is still plainly visible and discernable.

The case is a very snug fit. It requires a bit of effort to get the phone to snap into it, and once in there's little play between the edges of the case and the phone. This is not a case where the phone will slip out of the case in your pocket and there will be appreciably less dirt in the case as compared to more relaxed-fit cases.

The jury is out on how much protection it provides, but it seems to be decent, particularly for the cost. I like this case and prefer it over a more expensive case I have for my phone.

title_x: Easy to hold, doesn’t collect lint
text: I purchased this army green case because I can’t stand a thick case in my pocket.  This case is perfect for my needs.  It does not collect lint, yet it has texture enough to help you hang onto the phone.  The lip on the front of the case is only about a millimeter or so, but it serves to help protect the screen if dropped on a flat surface.  Other than this, there is no screen protection against direct blunt object strikes.  Still, a great case for the money and it will probably last me the life of the phone!

**edit** The vendor states that the case allows wireless (Qi) charging - I didn’t find that to be true. I was unable to charge my iPhone XR with this case installed using an Insignia 10w Qi pad. The iPhone charges fine using the same pad with the phone out of the case. (Still love the case - wireless charging isn’t a make/break thing for me. Just wanted to correct inaccurate information.)

title_x: Christmas gift (from my Mom) for my Dad
text:
The Amazon Premium Renewed gets 5 stars all on its own. If you can find a device with that, pay the extra (from 'just' Amazon Renewed) and get it! Also, absolutely cannot tell the phone was ever pre-owned or pre-used!!

The iPhone XR was an upgrade gift for my Dad from my Mom. His old device was an iPhone 6. He takes ALOT of photos. Every truck show, every tractor show, every time the grands are around, and all the weird bugs... he has pics - lol. And his iPhone 6 (8GB! Lol) ran into a conundrum: It was full of photos, so it didn't have space for his updates. And because it couldn't update, he couldn't upload his photos to the cloud. Also, he wanted a bigger screen. (I'm the same, why put on glasses when you can just have a bigger screen 🤷🏼‍♀️).

I honestly thought that the 'swipe the screen away' feature - replacing the home button - would drive him up the wall. He hasn't said a word! (BEEEEELIEVE me... he's at that wonderful, fully liberated age where he says whatever he thinks and does 👊🏻 not 👊🏻 care). He truly loves this phone! Score 1 for technology when an OG Baby Boomer embraces the ease of use, transitioning up (what?) 4 years in advancements and upgrades AND LIKES IT!!

text:
This Otterbox Symmetry case fits my Samsung Galaxy S9 perfectly. All ports are easily accessible. The sides are beefy and have a cut running around the edge that greatly increases grip on the phone. It will eventually collect pocket lint but seems easy to clean.
Buttons work perfectly. The opening for the camera, fingerprint reader and sensors is the best of the several cases I've tried. There's a nicely sloped bevel that allows your finger to easily and comfortably access the fingerprint sensor. This opening is one hole unlike many cases that have a piece of case unnecessarily dividing the opening (possibly interfering with the flash function).
The case is screen protector friendly coming right up to the edge of most protectors adding a good protective edge around the screen. The top and bottom of the case are raised several millimeters above the screen area keeping above any surface the phone is placed upon.
The Otterbox Symmetry is thick enough to inspire confidence in its protection but doesn't add a lot of weight or bulk.
The Symmetry case supports fast wireless charging. Mine works flawlessly with my Yootech charging stand.
I highly recommend this case.

This phone is the most I've ever spent on a phone and still much cheaper than buying new. I even upgraded to 64 GB because I know what happens when the memory starts to go as on the 32 GB I had on the old phone.

text: I have an 8 1/2 inch wrist so seeing that this band was compatible with up to 9 inches was a selling point. After receiving the band it is super tight on the absolute last notch. text:
I received a review sample in exchange for a review and have been having a blast with this simple-but-cool lens.

The instructions discuss screwing the lens into a "slim-line protective case" when in fact that case is actually the clip and mine came in the sealed package already installed. A few things you need to note:

- If you are using a protective case for your phone (I am using a [[ASIN:B009VKSVTC Evecase Leather Wallet Case with Stand and Credit Card Holder for Samsung Galaxy Note 2]]) you need to remove your phone before you can clip on this lens.

- This is a true fisheye lens that will capture a full 180 degrees. I took a shot of my music room, which normally takes three shots to fully capture and the one shot managed to include all of my amps, drums and instruments.

- There is NO magnification. This is a straight through lens with the fisheye effect as the only feature.

- Your photos will be framed in what will look like a black mat over a porthole. Sort of like a spy shot, and also ultra cool for some unique views of wide areas.

I am concerned that the clip extends over my screen on my phone. There is a soft plastic patch with a slight texture that holds the lens in place and seems to protect the lens from scratching. On the other hand I had to reposition the lens to get to my camera icon on the screen. Since this is a new tool I am sure I will discover convenient workarounds. If so I will be sure to update this review.

The package itself is simple: it comes with the lens pre-screwed into the clip, a small cloth bag and a lens cover. The latter is a nice touch. The price is nominal considering the quality of the photos I have taken with this already. In fact, I have been able to shoot some interesting pictures. It's a shame that Amazon has eliminated the customer-supplied image feature because a few pictures are worth thousands of words.

For the price you cannot go wrong. Especially if you are used to shooting multiple times to get an entire subject. The best thing I can say is had I not been provided with a review sample I would purchased one of these anyway. They are that useful in certain situations and very high quality.

title_x: Nice bands, fit my Series 6 40mm watch perfectly ...
text:
I decided to change out my standard-issue black silicone band for something more colorful and found these. My wrist tends to run a little large (around 8") and not all bands fit, so I figured elastic might be a good choice.

These are adjustable, so I'm able to get a precise comfortable fit. I also use several of the health tracking features (O2, pulse, and ECG) and fit is critical, especially for the O2 function. So far, this band is working even better than my old silicone band as I can get just the right "tightness" for the monitor to work. The O2 monitor is particularly finicky, and so far, it's working perfectly every time.

The bands are colorful, and since I tend to wear black slacks with bright solid jewel-tine tops, they fit my wardrobe, too. My only reservation on these is durability -- so far, I haven't noticed any problems, but I'm not certain they'll last more than a year or so. Time will tell. The cost isn't that great, so it's not a huge risk.

Overall, I really like these.

text:
I received this phone for Christmas and after 23 days, I love it! It's easy to use and I can make a call without having to take my glasses off. Yes, I'm a bit far-sighted. This is my first smart phone and I'm not all that interested in surfing or email, having a ton of apps, or even texting. I use a phone for making and getting calls and so far this one has been perfect.

The screen is bright, responsive and quick, the size, smaller than an iphone or galaxy, bigger than most non-smart phones is just right. It's easy to see and hold yet isn't so big it doesn't fit well in a pocket. The battery life is good. I haven't timed the battery life but it's good for at least 5 days on standby, probably more. Talking on it is the best part. It sounds great. Voices are clear and I've never had someone on the other end mention problems hearing me.

I count this phone as the best phone I've ever had. I couldn't be happier.

Update: Six months later and I still love it. But I've realized that with a touch screen I can't feel my way to the right button.

text:

It'd be a nice future addition though as the metal disc in my phone case that I use for my car mount, some reason it doesn't stick well to this battery pack. Like it barely sticks at all. But the magnet in my car- the phone case sticks to it extremely well for some reason. So just know you have to have the right sorta phone case if you want to attach this to your phone.

Battery wise- it came completely dead so I charged it up and it works well/ has a decent lifespan to it. The battery pack seems well made and looks nice.

title_x: Great Looking Case for iPhone 14 Pro
text:
When investing in something as valuable and important as an iPhone it’s important to protect it but, like most, I still want it to look good and even better add function.

This case does all of the above. The dual material covering looks terrific and thus far has held up well.

The space to hold cards is very convenient for carrying my most important cards with me often eliminating the need for me to carry my wallet separately.

While this is not the most protective case out there it does offer a fair amount of protection for the most vulnerable parts of the phone.

And it is compatible with screen protectors which is critical for me.

This is a case I recommend.

title_x: Great, but maybe try the longer one for Pixel XL (update: dead)
text:
Update 6/27/21
Charger stopped working this past week while on a trip. Just out of the blue, worked great every day for months and then just stopped. Charging pad indicates that it knows there but has an error (blinking light instead of solid light), and none of the portable wireless chargers (battery packs and my car charger) work with it anymore. Disappointed, it barely lasted 3 months.
Original review:
I got this to use with my wife's Pixel 3a XL, which lacks wireless charging.
Happy to say it works, even inside of a wallet case (although I need to pull some of the glue off the back of the wallet case to make it fit- best position seems to be in between the wallet material and the TPU case inside. If placed in the TPU, there are just too many layers and a good connection can't be made reliably). But, I should have opted maybe for a longer cable version. This one places the charging area on the lower third of the phone, which successfully avoids the finger print reader but also makes the phone kind of lopsided on the charger. If placed in the middle of the charging pad, the charging area of this adapter is too off-center to get power. I eventually found a way to make it work for her (I have a long double- space charging pad, and dropping it on there in any orientation seems to make contact), but I needed to fiddle with it before we had a system that works. It is now pretty convenient, and unlike other charging pads I'd try in the past that were cheaper (here and on ebay), this one hasn't burnt out after a few charges. Been using it for months now and so far so good!

text: I used TecArmor on my S3 for years and love it--I do swap them out about every 6 months as I usually scratch the cover or it gets dirty around the edges, but they aren't meant to be permanent, so I'm good with a three pack lasting a year and a half.  They are pretty easy (though nervewracking for an OCD sort like me!) to put on, and they protect very well.  My S3 still looks brand new after nearly 3 years of use, and I am happy knowing that my S6 should fare as well, given that I got these on as quickly as possible!

text:
This is a great car phone holder that works well for my Camaro. This works really well for me, so much better than the vent holders where I could only do landscape but never portrait format.

It opens and closes easily and automatically but also has a button to do so. It charges very fast. This is a great mount that can also be attached to the windshield if I want to but for now I am keeping it on the dashboard. Great find.

text:
I wanted to protect my new Galaxy S22 Ultra, so ordered this case. I am a klutz and my phone is often on the ground or floor. I owned a similar case for my Galaxy S20 Ultra, so I knew what I wanted.

The screws make me feel like my phone is secure. The metal case is sturdy and I love the rubber bumper. It helps me keep a secure grip on the phone. All of the cutouts fit perfectly. The case also has rubber closures for the stylus and charging receptacle. The stylus bumper came off during installation. The rubber charging bumper is a little hard to open, but I attribute that to being new. Opening the rubber charging stopper is getting a little easier each time I use it.

Misplaced the stylus bumper, so that’s still open. But overall, the case is attractive, protects my phone and it’s sturdy.

text: I’ve loved Otterbox cases for a long time, but this is the first one I’ve used that’s a bit of a miss. The way the inner rubber is made, of you have a cover on your screen, it pushes against it and separated it from the screen at the corners. The rubber is also flush with the screen, so there isn’t the best protection for the screen itself. The rubber where the volume buttons are also separates (or loosens) a bit too easily. It’s a decent case, but definitely overpriced.

text:
This charging station came on time and was well packaged.

Pros: Lightweight and the wireless charger works well on my iPhone. Fit really well on my bedside table.

Cons: It does not charge the Apple Watch and the AirPods at the same time. Be warned.

Overall this product does what it says it does minus it not charging the watch and AirPods at the same time. If you are looking for a cheap off brand dock station, this is for you!

No more charging interruption for more stable and efficient charging.', 'Camera Protection: iPhone 14 is finally here. Power up, protect, and connect your latest iPhone 14 with the apple charging station to get the most from your iPhone 14 experience. With the protruding design, it’s easy to pick up your devices and your phone’s camera gets maximum protection. This wireless charging pad is really a must-have for your new iPhone 14.', 'Safer & More Efficient Charging: Safety meets efficiency! The charging station for multiple devices is built in the upgraded smart chipset, providing overcharge protection, short circuit protection, overcurrent protection, overvoltage protection, temperature control, anti-interference protection and more. Experience wireless charging with total peace of mind (Note: This charging pad comes with a 24W adapter for more efficient charging).', 'Sleep-Friendly, Anti-Slip & Ultra-Portable: Stay charged with this magsafe charger whether you are in the office, at home or during travel! The indicator light will auto turns off after 20S to ensure a good sleep. Plus, you can enjoy on-the-go charging as this wireless iPhone charger is flat and lightweight to easily carry around.', 'Widely Compatible & Case Friendly: Born for Apple enthusiasts, this wireless charger for iPhone works flawlessly with iPhone 14/13/12 series, AirPods 3/Pro 2/Pro MagSafe, it will NOT work with other products not mentioned. In addition, the iPhone wireless charger can charge phones with MagSafe cases. Get rid of hassles of taking off the case to charge your phone every time!']

text:
I drive a Honda Element, and I was having a hard time finding a place to mount my phone; I used to have it on the dash, but it was too high and too far to reach properly.

This gadget allowed me to put my phone right on the air vent, which is easily accessible. At first I slid it into the middle of the vent but the weight made the vent close and the mount point downwards, so I moved it to the very bottom vent slat and it worked great.

I put the magnetic piece between my phone and the phone case - the case is a fairly thick rubber, so I didn't think it would stay in place. When I tested it the phone actually did stay on, but it would fall off if you really shook it. But for driving it's perfect. I also like how you don't have to actually stick the magnet to your phone or case if you don't want to - just slide it between.

title_x: Amazing - I can finally use my cell phone inside
text:
This was fairly easy to install - once we found out where the nearest cell tower was. After that, it was deciding where to put it so we wouldn't have cables all over the place. We attached the antenna to the roof (there was an exhaust pipe just where we needed one). We ran the cable inside and hooked it to the amplifier and ran a cable around the room to place the transmitter near the center of the house.

Prior to having this, if you wanted to talk on your cell, you had to hope the person on the other end would hold on long enough so you could get outside to talk. (Thank goodness it's Florida). Our house is new and it has some wonderful something in the roof to help dissipate the heat which totally blocks the cell signals. Add to the fact that we are in the middle of nowhere and cell towers are far apart, I wasn't actually sure this would work. But work it does and it's wonderful.

Now our phones ring inside, reception has gone from "no service" to full service and most importantly all calls are crisp, clear and easily understood (and we can talk inside).

It went up in a very short time, although we did take the instructions out and look them over so we knew what we were up against. It was very straightforward and getting onto the roof was the hardest part of the actual install. It went together easily and was up and running as soon as the connections were made. I did have to go out and purchase some cable holders because we went up and over door ways. I put a few of those plastic clips that stick to the wall in strategic places and we're good to go.

Our house is 3500 square feet and it's very long and narrow so I was a little uncertain if it would reach the outside edges but I was willing to settle for service in the main part of the house. No need to avoid "dead zones", we've walked the house from inch to inch and service never blinked. YAY!

If you aren't sure if it will work for you, take my word for it that I am not a techie in any way, shape or form. Instructions were clear, well written and easily understood. I did not need to call support for help in any way (I didn't think they'd come and climb on the roof) but once the two decisions were made: 1) where is the nearest cell tower; and 2) how do we run it for least problems with cables, the rest was just connecting cables. It did look a bit intimidating when it arrived but it was very straightforward and easy to install.

I'm going off now to make some cell calls, from my chair inside my house!

title_x: Remote does not work with DSLR Camera.
text: I ordered this 'Phone Tripod, Fugetek Phone & Camera Tripod with Bluetooth Remote Shutter (51")' for review. First off let me start by saying that I thought this would work with my DSLR camera however upon receiving the Tripod with Bluetooth Remote Shutter, I realized it is only for mobile phones connecting via Bluetooth - at least in my case. My DSLR camera does not have WiFi nor Bluetooth capabilities so I can not test if it would work on cameras that have those options. With that said, the remote does work great for my Android phone. There was no issues with it connecting at all and I will definitely be using it for taking pictures with my phone. The Tripod itself is very lightweight and fairly compact and will support my heavier DSLR camera, but I am not sure I would trust it for long exposures in any kind of breeze. Overall I do like this kit for what it is, and think it has useful value.

title_x: Great pouch for stashing your phone while hiking
text:
My current phone is a Motorola Moto X4 in a slim gel case. Approximate dimensions with case are: 5.9 x 3 x .4. It fits very well in the pouch - you might be able to go a bit wider/thicker, but not much longer.

I use this pouch to stash my smartphone while I'm out on a hike. Normally I keep my phone in a waterproof pouch, but I also throw my keys, wallet, and various small pocket tools in there so I don't have the extra weight/bulk on me while I'm walking, bouldering, etc.. So I wanted something which would also protect it from being scratched or dinged. This is great - light, a little padded, plenty of space.

Maybe it could be a little stiffer, I'd feel better if it was just a little more rigid and indeed might insert a pair of plastic panels into it, just to ward against the odd impact. But this is mostly fine as it is.

Would recommend.

title_x: Durable, grippable, easy to hold and use
text:
I purchased this for my mother's phone - her very first smartphone ever - about a year and change ago. It is helpful because it offers her something to grip the phone with, some additional protection against drops, and some resistance to other abrasion. The phone is still in good condition. She has arthritis so it is important that she is able to easily hold and manipulate the phone, and this case has the right texture and design to enable her to do so.

It also matches the case we got for her tablet.

Would recommend.

title_x: Beautiful phone. Too bad it crashes if you install apps. Yes, I'm talking about "Unfortunately My Launcher Has Stopped Working"
text:
Gorgeous phone, nice specs, if only it worked. Seriously, My Launcher crashes--you know the thing that runs the home screen. Kinda basic requirement to have a functional launcher. All manner of apps crash. I mean, I should say, if you don't install any apps, it works fine. If you want to install apps on this phone--and you do, that's why you got a phone with 64GB of storage--then it kinda sucks as a phone capable of running basic apps like news, weather, and clock.

I called Blu. They were open, and it didn't take long for me to get a human being. But they told me to do basic stuff I'd already done--like I've done factory reinstalls and done all the stuff the internet suggests. So they had me email them screenshots with info about my phone, of error messages, and info about the apps that were crashing. After 20 screenshots, I'd had enough screenshotting stuff going wrong.

You know what? THEY SENT ME INSTRUCTIONS ON HOW TO RESET THE BLU LIFE ONE X2. Not the MINI. I mean, sure, I can do another hard reset, but I don't imagine it's going to make a difference coz I've already done plenty of hard resets.

BLU, get it together.

text:
In my honest opinion the difficulty of this is enough for someone to get a license doing it and offering to install it for you in a phone store. There is a LOT that can go wrong, i tried 3 times, twice because there are two glass protectors and once more when i went for the warranty. (which costs 10$ for them to ship another one)
first, its obviously not cheap, and theres not much i can think of other than the gimmicky UV light thing that would make it cost so much.
second, its VERY difficult to install without dust if you live somewhere dusty in general, had to learn this the hard way, i guess thats my problem though.
More importantly, the adhesive given is often not enough and doesn't actually spread all the way. After some hours of googling AFTER i screwed up 3 times, i learned that you're supposed to tilt the phone to help the adhesive move along... couldn't find that anywhere except from a random reddit post, so even then i'm not sure.

Either way i'm obviously not a trained professional to install this and i can only hope you manage to become one within the span of your 2 attempts.

text:
This charger has some very nice features and does exactly what you would expect from a wireless car charger.

The phone that I was using to test this was a Galaxy S8, which supports 10w wireless charging. I can say this charger was able to get close to that with peaks of 9.4w observed. The automatic feature of the charger is very convenient although it will be interesting to see how it holds up. I have tried this charger with a larger phone (iPhone 8 plus) and the charger has just enough space for it, but it does work. I would be careful when placing the ball mount into the socket and I recommend doing so when the plastic is warm or at least at room temperature to avoid one of the 4 clamps breaking. Trust me, I have had it happen with other mounts.

Mount Options:
The mounts included are nice, but the vent one is a bit bulky. It will not work in my vents, but I haven't found a mount that will work so I'm not really upset about this. The suction cup is nice, but I know from experience with other suction cup mounts they will fail in really hot or really cold temperatures. I have will be using this in another car that the vent mount will work and print a cup holder mount for my main car.

Overall:
I’m happy with this charger and will be using it on my hour plus drive to work. I will update this review if the product fails.

text:
I am not a phone gamer or anything, but I have a bunch of apps that I need:
authenticators, Outlook, Gmail, the app I use to pay my rent and put in repair tickets with my landlord company, a banking app, the app I use to track my weight on my bluetooth scale, chat apps for work and family, etc, and this one is speedy for all of them.
It's not too heavy, it's not too large or small, (see attached picture for scale).
The UI is really close to my previous Samsung Android experience.
The last phone I had (Samsung Galaxy A6 Plus (SM-A605G/DS) 4GB / 32GB)
had finally started to slow down and have trouble since it only had 32 GB internal storage.
But I have a good feeling about this one, I think this one should last a few years for me.
I am very happy I could get a replacement for under 200 dollars.

text:
Absolute garbage instructions, installation.

All 3 wasted by 2 people trying to install this screen protector. I've done plastic, dry install, wet install, glass... This is the absolute worse installation method I've ever tried.

Watched video 2 times, pausing, attempting to understand the method. I couldn't tell you how the protector is, it simply would not install as shown. Only tab to peel correctly (per the video) was tab 1. Tab 2 pulled film and didn't even behave as theirs did in the video. For the life of me I've looked at the design and can't understand why this is so difficult.

2nd protector had tab 2 break off when pulled.

By the 3rd I was so frustrated that after pulling tab 2 again and having no effect after using the squeegee, I almost (but didn't) threw my phone.

Wife and I did step by step, pausing only to have this product end up stuck to it's backing and not the phone.

Don't waste your money. I can't figure how it has positive reviews. Out of the past 10 years of buying protectors, this is hands down the worst I've purchased.

text: The OtterBox Symmetry Clear case is snappy looking. The lines that are a fine glitter stripe in two different colors looks good. It will look really good on a dark colored phone. All of the cutouts are where they need to be and the case is slim and scratch resistant. This case also offers drop protection. Now for the bad part. The sound buttons are difficult to use. You have to remove the case to charge with the fast charger. The constant removal and replacement is sure to make a potential issue with fit. As for protection, if you also get a tempered glass protector, you will probably never have any breakage if you drop the phone. Now, if you run over with your car (I did that once) you can pretty much figure you will need a new phone.

text:
I liked the “soap bubble” look online, but in person it just doesn’t look nice. It completely obscures the pretty ‘sierra blue’ of my phone, and makes it look pink, with a weird geometric pattern.

I could probably live with that, as it does seem like a case that would protect my phone from damage, but it has a very wide cutout for the camera lenses, with squared, rather than rounded edges. Aside from the fact that my mild ocd can’t tolerate it, it also leaves space for dust and whatever to get into the case, and scratch my phone.

And ohhhh the fingerprints! I’ve gotten used to most things having an anti-fingerprint coating that minimizes the smudged look. Turns out, that’s become important to me. I’m not a fan of the smudges.

All that aside, it’s definitely functional as a MagSafe case. It has no trouble at all sticking to the charger.

Buyer beware though… you can return it, as I am doing, but you have to print a label and package it, with its RMA. You won’t be able to just drop it at ups for them to pack it.

text:
I urge you to skip this product.

The leather, which it might actually be, is not soft, and will probably fall apart with few hours of use. The inside of the band; you know, the part against your skin... feels like sand paper. It's unfinished and not sealed with any kind of leather treatment.

The edges of the band have a distinctly sharp feel to them, and there's no way that will feel ok when my wrist is bending or turning.

Since I was looking for something comfortable enough to wear all day, and/or night, I can assure you that this watchband is not it.

The only thing left to decide is whether or not it's worth a trip to UPS in order to return it.

title_x: Very slow, no tap-to-pay, sent it back
text: My last 5 phones have been Motorolas. I like the combination of solid features at a decent price point. This phone, however, did not meet my expectations. It's extremely slow and laggy with even basic tasks like shopping on Amazon. The battery life was good, but did not reach the advertised 2 days. But the kicker was that this phone does not have NFC, so there is no tap-to-pay feature. I did a little research and found a Samsung Galaxy A32 that is much faster, has tap-to-pay, and is an all-around upgrade to this phone. It was $35 more, but well worth it. Glad I made this purchase on Amazon as the return/exchange was easy.

text: I am very hard on my phones, I drop them often and the tempered glass covers always crack. I was so happy to find this cover and I love the neutral color. I don't like a flashy case and this fits the bill.  The cover protects the screen and the whole phone. I LOVE the dial feature to turn the phone on silent - its actually easier than the switch with a cover on it. The phone charges easily with the contact type chargers or the plug type chargers.  I have taken this in my pool and the waterproof claim is true. Not a drop inside the case. Ev en though my iphone is waterproof. I feel so much better with the protection this case provides. My phone was expensive and this case was so worth the money as it protects my phone, keeping it looking new.  I was able to put a magnetic disc on the case for my car holder without a problem, it sticks well.

title_x: Galaxy S10 is a solid Android phone
text:
Got this slighlty used phone for my wife as a replacement for a Samsung Galaxy S8.

The screen size is not overly large, which works with her sensibilities of not wanting to carry around a mega screen phone.

The fingerprint reader, screen brightness and choices to customize the phone to her liking is what my wife likes about the phone. The 128GB internal storage works perfect for app installs & the like.

However, the big bonus is the inclusion of a microSD card slot. This allows a person to add a ton of more storage at a lower price point that buying the phone with more internal storage. Internal storage may be faster, but in the value-vs-reward trade-off, I'd rather have the extra space at lower cost. My wife agrees, as the 256GB microSD card I installed satisfies all of her storage requirements.

The Samsung Galaxy S21 is now selling, so this review may not be as relevant anymore. However, anyone looking for a good Android phone without the high price should give the Galaxy S10 a serious look.

description: ["Samsung's flagship for 2019, the Galaxy S10, matches its powerful hardware with the fresh OneUI interface. This thin and light phone is powered by the powerful Snapdragon 855/Exynos 9820 chips and has heaps of memory for your multitasking needs - a whopping 8GB, accompanied by 128 or 512GB versions. Design-wise, the Galaxy S10 sets itself apart from the previous generation with its offset punch-hole 10MP selfie camera, which is capable of capturing stabilized 4K footage. The camera is the only thing interrupting the gorgeous 6.1-inch OLED display. The cameras at the back are three - the regular 12MP is joined by a 12MP telephoto and a 16MP wide-angle one, a first for the Galaxy S series."]
